text: Lepeshkino () is a rural locality (a village) in Baymurzinsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 299 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 53 km from Mishkino, 9 km from Baymurzino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Lepeshkino
